-- Spain to Make 6,000 Union Members Return to Work, Mundo Reports
-- B y   M a n u e l   B a i g o r r i
-- 2012-07-18T06:48:37Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-18/spain-to-make-6-000-union-members-return-to-work-mundo-reports.html
Spain  will make 6,000 public-sector
workers, two thirds of those who devote their time to union
duties, return to work starting Oct. 1,  El Mundo  reported.  The plan will generate savings of 252 million euros ($309
million), the newspaper said, citing data from the Budget
Ministry.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Manuel Baigorri in Madrid at 
 mbaigorri@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Kenneth Wong at 
 kwong11@bloomberg.net  